Class MOGPAlgorithm

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IAlgorithm, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.IPopulation, net.sf.jclec.ISystem, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC, IMOAlgorithm, net.sf.jclec.util.random.IRandGenFactory

    public class MOGPAlgorithm
extends MOECAlgorithm
    Multi-objective Genetic Programming (GP) Algorithm. The current implementation defines the same iterative process of a GA, where offspring are created applying recombination and mutation operators with a specific probability. This class can be an extension point for developers that need another kind of GP operators like permutation, editing or encapsulation.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.
